&lt;p&gt;The word &amp;ldquo;Chasing&amp;rdquo; means &lt;a href="https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BA%BA%E9%97%B4%E8%AF%8D%E8%AF%9D#%E7%8E%8B%E5%9B%BD%E7%BB%B4%E7%BE%8E%E5%AD%A6"&gt;&amp;ldquo;衣带渐宽终不悔，为伊消得人憔悴&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
The suffix &amp;ldquo;1020&amp;rdquo; is used only to avoid duplication of names, and &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October_20"&gt;October 20th&lt;/a&gt; is my birthday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id="about-me"&gt;About me&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;🎓 I am a Ph.D. candidate in Computer Science and Technology at the &lt;a href="http://www.ict.cas.cn/"&gt;Institute of Computing Technology, Chinese Academy of Sciences&lt;/a&gt; (since 2023), co-advised by &lt;a href="https://ictxh.github.io/"&gt;Xiaohui Peng&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://novel.ict.ac.cn/zxu/"&gt;Zhiwei Xu&lt;/a&gt;. Prior to that, I received my B.Eng. in Computer Science and Technology from &lt;a href="https://www.shu.edu.cn/"&gt;Shanghai University&lt;/a&gt; (2019 — 2023).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;🔭 My research focuses on distributed systems and machine learning systems. I am currently working on training and inference optimization for LLMs, with a particular focus on &lt;strong&gt;RL systems for Agentic AI&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Friends</title><link>https://chasing1020.github.io/friends/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chasing1020.github.io/friends/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;🔗 I would appreciate it if you could add my blog to your links.&lt;/p&gt;
